  "text": "Remark 2.10. In [CITATION_1] , deriving the Hamilton-Jacobi equation in the finite horizon case is more difficult. Indeed, taking into account trajectories which oscillate around the junction point (Zeno phenomenon) induce some technical difficulties.",
